race.comment: TIME ALLOWED (1) is the interesting one. He makes his Aus debut for the Busuttin & Young camp having looked talented in three runs in the UK, winning his maiden at Southwell All Weather dominantly as favourite. He's jumped out well enough for this and it wouldn't shock if he proved too strong for the locals. VALEDICTORIAN (4) broke through for a deserved maiden win here last time out and did it easily, scoring by 3.5 lengths. He can go on with it now. EDEN ROSE (10) bolted in with a soft maiden two back, measuring up well at Flemington at 100-1 last time. This is easier, a repeat goes close. NAVY NINA (8) was just fair fresh but can improve off that.
